      • getClusterGeom

        public GM_Polygon getClusterGeom()
        Returns a Polygon of the cluster. This polygon is created from a buffer (size 4 by default) if the cluster contains only a node (i.e. a Point geometry type), or two nodes (i.e. a Segment geometry type). If the cluster contains strictly more than two nodes, the polygon is created from the convex hull of the cluster, except the case where all nodes in the cluster are in the same straight line. In this last problematic case, the geometry is computed with a buffer (size 4 by default).
        Returns:
        a polygon which represents graphically the cluster in order to correctly display it.
